Provides 'MathJax' and macros to enable its use within Rd files for rendering equations in the HTML help files.

name: r-mathjaxr
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.2-0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-mathjaxr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/mathjaxr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/mathjaxr/mathjaxr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: e7d58b89ac2380ee651aad0b312bb3a9ed732467f99452f6dbd5c8ead7e8e1f9

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('mathjaxr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('mathjaxr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/wviechtb/mathjaxr
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: Provides 'MathJax' and macros to enable its use within Rd files for rendering equations in the HTML help files.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
